2. (1) In this Order – 

“Act of 1993” means the Statistics Act 1993 (No. 21 of 1993); 

“day of the week” means a Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, 
Saturday or Sunday; 

“direction” means a direction under section 26 of the Act of 1993 made pursuant 
to the requirement prescribed under Article 4; 

“Regulation” means Regulation (EU) 2019/2152 of the European Parliament and 
of the Council of 27 November 20191 as amended by Commission Delegated 
Regulation (EU) 2021/1704 of 14 July 20212; 

“relevant aggregate figure” means, in relation to a day of the week, the aggregate 
of the turnover achieved on that day of the week in each week of 2021; 

“relevant period” means such period occurring in 2021 as the Director General 
may specify in the notice of a direction; 

“survey” means the Trading Day and Product Profile Survey that is conducted 
by the Central Statistics Office for the purpose of obtaining, including for the 
purposes of compliance with the Regulation, the information specified in the 
Schedule. 

(2) A word or expression that is used in this Order and also used in the 
Regulation has the same meaning in this Order as in the Regulation, other than 
where the context otherwise requires.
